A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Naval mines continue to be a cost-effective way to deter or control adversary movements, including surface ships and submarines. Aerial deployment of mines is an
expeditious and efficient way to deliver large numbers of mines to planned minefields. Major efforts under the Long Range Aerial Delivery Maritime Mine (LRADMM)
program will yield increased capability for the entire QS Family of Mines are:
1) Quickstrike Extended Range (QS-ER) M-Code: M-Code GPS antijam capabilities will be integrated into the QS-ER guidance kit and wing assembly to increase
precision placement capabilities for 2000lb mines in GPS-denied environments.
2) Quickstrike Long Range (QS-LR) Powered Delivery Vehicle: A powered delivery vehicle will be developed to carry an in-service Mk 62 500lb mine to water entries
that are 300 nm+ downrange, significantly decreasing risk to the launch delivery platform.
3) Increased launch-platform integration: Integration work for QS-ER will start for B-2. Integration with F/A-18 E/F will start for QS-LR.

