B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                          FY 2027     FY 2027       FY 2027
                                                                                                                   FY 2025   FY 2026      Base        OOC           Total
Continue the RAM "Performance Lab" to provide quick turnaround raid performance curves which guide
integration, tactics, and future investments decisions, including software improvement decisions. Continue to
conduct experiments to verify the modeling and simulation indicating performance improvements are grounded
in actual testing. The major efforts are a continuation of the analysis of backlogged Red Sea engagement data
to inform software improvements for the RAM Software Factory and conduct a flight test with SW 7.10. The flight
test will verify the performance improvements implemented and provide an opportunity for further learning.

Continue Software Factory efforts to deliver software performance updates incorporating improvements
identified through trade studies and flight tests. Develop and release two RAM Block 2B missile software
updates SW 7.10 and SW 7.11.

Continue SKIP development to update weapon specifications and guidelines of effective use to support design
reviews. Continue development of missile and launcher software that leverages Uplink/Downlink hardware
capabilities to provide in-flight RAMs with continuous target data. Finalize Uplink/Downlink receiver and
antenna Proof of Design to support design reviews, testing and transition to Proof of Manufacturing Hardware
procurement. Complete GTV-1 development flight test, lab integration testing and risk reduction testing to
validate the quality of design, inform software development and support design reviews. Conduct Critical Design
Review to demonstrate that system detailed design and test plans are complete, meet requirement and have
acceptable risk. Begin planning for FY 2027 development flight test.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
Continue RAM GMWS integration efforts to support (1) RAM BLK 1A, 2, 2A and 2B into AEGIS BL9.C3.x to
support RAM deployment on DDGs, (2) SSDS BL 12 Integration, Development Test (DT) and Operational Test
(OT) events on Ship Self Defense Test Ship (SDTS) and Combat System Ship Qualification Test (CSSQT) and
(3) SKIP model development efforts to support future RAM BLK 2C Combat System Integration and testbed
efforts.

Continue the RAM "Performance Lab" to collect, review and analyze real world data that can be inform the RAM
SW Factory to expedite the delivery of fixes and improvements against evolving threats. Leverage Modeling
and Simulation (M&S) to develop and analyze RAM raid performance curves and conduct experiments to verify
the M&S indicating performance improvements are grounded in actual testing. FY 2027 will include a focus on
concept exploration for future Software/Hardware development of the next generation of the RAM GMWS.



