A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This project provides the Preliminary and Contract design and Class test efforts for the Ship to Shore Connector (SSC) Program. The SSC is an aluminum air-cushion
vehicle (hovercraft) designed to enhance the Navy and Marine Corps' capability to execute a broad spectrum of missions from humanitarian assistance to major combat.
Its primary role is to efficiently transport weapon systems, equipment, cargo, and personnel of the Marine Air/Ground Task Force. As a high-speed, amphibious craft, it
projects power by being fully compatible with all allied amphibious ships, while performing assaults and operational maneuvers from ship to shore and across the beach.
SSC provides the functional replacement for the Landing Craft, Air Cushion (LCAC) Class of ships, which began reaching extended service life in 2015. For FY 2015 and
beyond, this project will provide for Class Test and Evaluation of components and systems, as well as all programmatic effort and support activities necessary for the
development and execution of Class Test and Evaluation (T&E) plans and programs.

