A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Department of the Navy (DON) SBIR Program is a mission-oriented program that delivers innovative solutions to Naval requirements through a three-phase
competitive awards process. Qualified small business concerns propose dual-use solutions, that primarily address naval needs, to Research and Development (R&D)
topics aligned to Program Offices with resources to transition R&D-developed technology to warfighting capability. The SBIR Program requires each Federal agency
that has an extramural budget for Research and Development in excess of $100,000,000 to set aside 3.2% for SBIR to engage domestic small businesses in Federal
Research/Research and Development (R/R&D) and chart a path toward commercialization. The program's statutory goals are to stimulate technological innovation;
increase small business participation in federally funded R&D; and increase private sector commercialization of federal R&D.

