A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Project 1265 SubTDS
The first effort of the overall SubTDS program focuses on delivering full ICL functionality to all submarines in the fleet via the ADC MK5 effort. The ADC MK5
incorporates new adaptive technologies in a three-inch diameter form factor and will evolve through software/hardware upgrades, improved mobility, combat control
system integration via ICL, and enhanced functionality to counter advancing torpedo threats.

ADC MK6 effort focuses on developing an ECL hosted 6-inch acoustic countermeasure to supersede the ADC MK3.

PMS415 STEB effort is limited to the development of changes to the ICL, specifically the breech door, to provide a stand-alone power and communications capability to
the payload through the ICL via a TEMPALT, with funding ending in FY 2026.

