FY 2026 Plans: - Initiated research for commonality with other Services and support emergent requirements for
Force Design in distributed operations cold weather environments. Conduct material tests of emerging materials
and technology to enhance existing cold weather clothing and equipment effectiveness while lightening the load
of the individual Marine. This includes soft shell fabrics to increase wind resistance, moisture management, and
durability; next generation low bulk insulation that increases warmth without sacrificing maneuverability and
integrating lightweight, high-performance fibers that improve survivability in subzero environments.
-Initiated to update design and materials that will be aligned with DLA sustainment requirements.
                                                                                  Congressional Adds Subtotals           0.000       2.413$$, NULL, $$The Cold Weather and Mountaineering (CWM) Program is centered on agility and efficiency utilizing various acquisition strategies. The CWM program leverages existing
developments and mature technologies from the commercial sector, which significantly shortens the government's research and development timeline. Contracting is
performed by either Marine Corps Systems Command or U.S. Army Natick Soldier Research, Development, and Engineering Center.

