D. Acquisition Strategy
The Light Armored Vehicle (LAV) Modification program is essential for keeping the legacy Light Armored Vehicle (LAV) fleet, originally built in 1983, operationally
effective until its planned retirement in FY 2039. It funds critical upgrades to vehicles, communications, and weapon systems to manage obsolescence, enhance safety,
and maintain network connectivity. To ensure effective fleet life-cycle management, the LAV Modification program resources a wide range of essential engineering
actions. These activities include managing platform and C4ISR obsolescence, implementing safety modifications, and maintaining critical network credentials like the
Authority to Operate (ATO) and Authority to Connect (ATC). The program also covers data management for all technical, engineering, and end-item products, as well as
the upkeep of support equipment and tools.




