FY 2026 Plans: This effort will be dedicated to the systems engineering and software development required
to integrate Unmanned Aerial System (UAS) Command and Control (C2) capabilities directly into the Maritime
Tactical Command and Control (MTC2) suite. This involves designing the system architecture, developing core
mission planning functionalities within the Tactical Planning Tool (TPT), and building the necessary Application
Programming interfaces (APIs), which will conclude with demonstration in a government designated environment
in 4QFY26.
Congressional Add: Unmanned ISR and Contested Logistics                                                                   0.000        9.654
FY 2025 Accomplishments: N/A
FY 2026 Plans: This effort will focus on the rapid development of a prototype Unmanned Aerial System (UAS)
for Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR) and aerial resupply missions by integrating vendor-
provided software onto government-selected airframes, purchase up to five units for on-shore testing, and
conducting spiral software improvements, all culminating in an initial demonstration in a designated government
environment in 4QFY26.
                                                                                 Congressional Adds Subtotals             0.000       19.307$$, NULL, $$Congressional Add funds under MTC2 PE 0608231N acquisition strategy aligns to DoDI 5000.87 Operation of the Software Acquisition Pathway in FY 2021. MTC2
executes an agile software development that is responsive to fleet needs. Instead of operating under Joint Capabilities Integration and Development System (JCIDS)
procedures, OPNAV N9DW directs MTC2's capability requirements through a Capability Needs Statement (CNS). Capability areas identified in the CNS direct the
Minimum Viable Capability Releases (MVCRs) delivered by the program. MTC2's contract strategy for product delivery includes Other Transaction Authority (OTA) and
Multiple Award Contract (MAC) vehicles to procure software development services. Pacific (NIWC-PAC), San Diego, CA is the designated Software Support Activity
(SSA).

