 currently installed in the Fleet through Continuous Improvement/Continuous Delivery (CI/CD). By digitally enabling the horizontal across Joint Forces and vertical
 across the Echelons alignment of capabilities, the acceleration of MTC2 requirements and enablement of operational Battle Management Aids will enhance operational
 effectiveness during a wartime posture. MTC2 funding increased in FY 2027 and FY 2028 to support the acceleration effort for Rapid Operational Planning (OneBrief).
 In FY 2027, funding will be utilized for the procurement of Commercial off the Shelf (COTS) software, tools, integration, and services. In addition, in FY 2027, MTC2 will
 support INDOPACOM's operations across three Pacific Fleet Maritime Operations Centers (MOCs), with expansion plans to six MOCs in FY 2028.

(Project 9999) This Congressional Add provides for the demonstration of a ship-integrated coaxial drone prototype for autonomous Intelligence, Surveillance
and Reconnaissance (ISR). This project will integrate Command and Control (C2), rigorous on-shore testing, and a final proof-of-concept demonstration within a
representative fleet operational environment. The project directly supports the Chief of Naval Operations' objectives for Joint All-Domain Command and Control (JADC2)
objectives in preparation for a 2027 peer or near-peer conflict.

