D. Acquisition Strategy
Congressional Add funds under MTC2 PE 0608231N acquisition strategy aligns to DoDI 5000.87 Operation of the Software Acquisition Pathway in FY 2021. MTC2
executes an agile software development that is responsive to fleet needs. Instead of operating under Joint Capabilities Integration and Development System (JCIDS)
procedures, OPNAV N9DW directs MTC2's capability requirements through a Capability Needs Statement (CNS). Capability areas identified in the CNS direct the
Minimum Viable Capability Releases (MVCRs) delivered by the program. MTC2's contract strategy for product delivery includes Other Transaction Authority (OTA) and
Multiple Award Contract (MAC) vehicles to procure software development services. Pacific (NIWC-PAC), San Diego, CA is the designated Software Support Activity
(SSA).




