to exceed the design life in 2034. MH-60 SLAP is comprised of two distinct assessments: investigative inspections and analysis of fleet assets, which will identify current
trends that either prohibit the MH-60 from reaching its design life or the required life based on operational inventory requirements; and forward-looking analysis, which
will identify future risks not yet realized on fleet assets. These assessments will consider the fatigue life of airframe structure as well as the health of aircraft subsystems.

