D. Acquisition Strategy
The ACAT II JPALS V2 program will modernize and enhance a critical ship and air platform capability. The program leverages prior Technology Maturation and Risk
Reduction (TMRR) efforts and proceeds with Engineering Development Model (EDM) development and testing. Milestone B was achieved March 2026 and Milestone
C is planned for 3Q FY2029. Given limited ship availability and low procurement quantities, Full Rate Production is not planned. A sole-source contract will be awarded
to Collins Aerospace, Fullerton, California, in March 2026. This contract will encompass the design, engineering, integration, and testing of Military GPS (M-Code)
functionality into the JPALS AN/USN-3(V)1, SSLS, including Onboard Repair Parts kits and Depot spares. This effort ensures the system's ability to leverage M-Code for
precision approach and landing operations while retaining legacy GPS functionality. Additional contract award planned for July 2026. This contract will encompass the
design, engineering, integration and testing of a software defined radio and LANTERNS waveform that will be supported by a Data Link Interface. This effort ensures the
system's ability to support MQ-25A in all operational environments. Both of these efforts will be baselined together at Critical Design Review. Fleet deployment will be
facilitated through retrofit kits, projected at an annual procurement and installation rate of 3-5 units.




